@@TJvBalloonHint.OnBalloonClick
Summary
  Occurs when the user clicks the balloon.
Description
  Use the OnBalloonClick to respond when the user clicks the balloon. Note that no OnBalloonClick is
  fired when the user clicks the close button on the balloon hint. Use the OnCloseBtnClick event handler
  to respond when the user clicks the close button.
Note
  This event does <i>not</i> occur for application hint windows, only for balloon hints launched with a call
  to ActivateHint, ActivateHintRect etc.
See Also
  OnCloseBtnClick, OnDblClick
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvBalloonHint.OnClose
Summary
  Occurs when the balloon closes.
Description
  Use OnClose to perform special processing when the balloon closes.
Note
  This event does <i>not</i> occur for application hint windows, only for balloon hints launched with a call
  to ActivateHint, ActivateHintRect etc.
See Also
  OnCloseBtnClick
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvBalloonHint.OnCloseBtnClick
Summary
  Occurs when close is attempted by clicking the close button.
Description
  Use OnCloseBtnClick to specify the conditions under which the balloon hint can close. An
  OnCloseBtnClick event handler returns a Boolean CanClose value that determines whether
  the hint is allowed to close. Its default value is true.

  Include boShowCloseBtn in Options, otherwise no close button is shown.
Note
  This event does <i>not</i> occur for application hint windows, only for balloon hints launched with a call
  to ActivateHint, ActivateHintRect etc.
See Also
  OnBalloonClick, OnClose, Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvBalloonHint.OnDblClick
Summary
  Occurs when the user double-clicks the balloon.
Description
  Use the OnDblClick to respond when the user double-clicks the balloon. Note that no OnDblClick is
  fired when the user clicks the close button on the balloon hint. Use the OnCloseBtnClick event handler
  to respond when the user clicks the close button.
Note
  This event does <i>not</i> occur for application hint windows, only for balloon hints launched with a call
  to ActivateHint, ActivateHintRect etc.
See Also
  OnBalloonClick, OnCloseBtnClick
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvBalloonHint.OnMouseDown
Summary
  Occurs when the user presses a mouse button with the mouse pointer over a balloon hint.
Description
  Use the OnMouseDown event handler to implement any special processing that should occur as a result
  of pressing a mouse button.

  The OnMouseDown event handler can respond to left, right, or center mouse button presses and shift
  key plus mouse-button combinations. Shift keys are the Shift, Ctrl, and Alt keys. X and Y are
  the pixel coordinates of the mouse pointer in the client area of the Sender.
Note
  This event does <i>not</i> occur for application hint windows, only for balloon hints launched with a call
  to ActivateHint, ActivateHintRect etc.
See Also
  OnBalloonClick, OnMouseUp
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvBalloonHint.OnMouseMove
Summary
  Occurs when the user moves the mouse pointer while the mouse pointer is over a balloon hint.
Description
  Use the OnMouseMove event handler to respond when the mouse pointer moves after the balloon hint has
  captured the mouse.

  Use the Shift parameter of the OnMouseMove event handler, to determine to the state of the shift
  keys and mouse buttons. Shift keys are the Shift, Ctrl, and Alt keys or shift key-mouse button
  combinations. X and Y are pixel coordinates of the new location of the mouse pointer in the client
  area of the Sender.
Note
  This event does <i>not</i> occur for application hint windows, only for balloon hints launched with a call
  to ActivateHint, ActivateHintRect etc.
See Also
  OnMouseDown, OnMouseUp
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvBalloonHint.OnMouseUp
Summary
  Occurs when the user releases a mouse button that was pressed with the mouse pointer
  over a balloon hint.
Description
  Use an OnMouseUp event handler to implement special processing when the user releases
  a mouse button.

  The OnMouseUp event handler can respond to left, right, or center mouse button presses and
  shift key plus mouse-button combinations. Shift keys are the Shift, Ctrl, and Alt keys. X and Y
  are the pixel coordinates of the mouse pointer in the client area of the Sender.
Note
  This event does <i>not</i> occur for application hint windows, only for balloon hints launched with a call
  to ActivateHint, ActivateHintRect etc.
See Also
  OnMouseDown, OnBalloonClick
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvBalloonHint.Options
Summary
  Determines the appearance and behavior of balloon windows displayed by calling
  ActivateHint, ActivateHintPos or ActivateHintRect.
Description
  Use the Options property to customize the appearance and functionality of balloon windows displayed
  by calling ActivateHint, ActivateHintPos or ActivateHintRect. Use these flags to

  * Specify whether to use the default values as specified by DefaultHeader, DefaultIcon
    and DefaultImageIndex.
  * Specify whether to play a sound and/or use custom special effect when a balloon window displays.
    Custom special effects are only available on windows XP systems: Note that because the balloon
    windows have a drop shadow, using custom animation may produces visually
    distracting, jerky animations.
  * Specify whether to show a close button in the balloon window.
See Also
  ApplicationHintOptions
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvBalloonHint.UseBalloonAsApplicationHint
Summary
  Specifies whether to use the balloon window as standard hint window for the application.
Description
  Use UseBalloonAsApplicationHint to specify whether to use the balloon window as standard hint
  window for the application. Use the ApplicationHintOptions to alter the appearance and
  behavior of balloon shaped application hint windows.
See Also
  ApplicationHintOptions
